The paper discusses the design and implementation of a Grid operating system, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the system architecture and implementation, which falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). Additionally, the paper discusses the support for major types of applications and the ease of deployment and maintenance, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the autonomic and scalable Grid architectures, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.Distributed). Finally, the paper discusses the plug-and-play Grid computing, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
